The Snorre A offshore oil platform is unlikely to resume production this week after being shut down by a natural gas leak because more time is needed to review plans.
Norway's daily oil production was down by an estimated 4 percent after a gas leak forced Statoil ASA to shut down one of its platforms in the North Sea.
Norway is the third crude exporter after Saudi Arabia and Russia and produces nearly three million barrels per day.
We are still working on securing the well, Statoil spokesman Kristofer Hetland told AFP.
